Trim the @green beans{80} then halve. Halve the @pak choi{1} lengthways. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @red chilli{1/2} lengthways, deseed then finely chop.

Pour the cold @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a #tight-fitting lid{}. Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g} and @salt{0.25%tsp}, cover with the lid and bring to the boil on medium-high heat. Once boiling, turn the heat down to its lowest setting. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, drain the @firm tofu{280%g} then pat dry with #kitchen paper{}. Chop into 2cm cubes. Pop the tofu into a #bowl{} with the @cornflour{10%g} and @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix well to coat the tofu. Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, add the tofu pieces to the pan. Fry until slightly crispy, ~{8-10%minutes}. Carefully turn every ~{1-2%minutes} to ensure they don't burn. Remove the tofu from the pan to a #plate{} and wipe out the pan.

Return the #frying pan{} to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. Once hot, lay in the bok choy, cut-side down. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook for ~{2%minutes}, then turn over and cook for another ~{2%minutes} on the other side. The bok choy should be slightly browned and charred. Add a splash of @water{50%ml} and pop a #lid{} (or some #foil{}) on the pan and leave to steam for another ~{3%minutes}. Remove the bok choy to a plate and cover with foil to keep warm.

Wipe out and return the pan to a medium-high heat. When the pan is hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the @Indonesian style spice mix{1%portion}, @ginger puree{1%portion} and garlic. Stir-fry for a further ~{1%minute}. Add the @coconut milk{200%ml}, @soy sauce{25%ml} and @water{50%ml}. Bring to a boil and turn the heat down, simmer until slightly thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

When everything is ready, stir the tofu through your curry, ensuring it is piping hot. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fluff the rice and share between your #bowls{}. Top with the tofu curry and bok choy, and sprinkle over the chilli. Enjoy!

> You can adjust the amount of chilli to your preferred spice level.